    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2009-03-30</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2009-04-30T16:20:14Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Stopping Trained in America Ph.D.s From Leaving the Economy Act of 2009 or the STAPLE Act - Amends the Immigration and Nationality Act to exempt from: (1) direct numerical limitations aliens who have earned a Ph.D. degree in science, technology, engineering, or mathematics from a U.S. institution of higher education and who have an offer of employment from a U.S. employer in a field related to such degree; and (2) H-1B visa (specialty occupation) numerical limitations aliens who have earned a Ph.D. degree in science, technology, engineering, or mathematics from a U.S. institution of higher education and with respect to whom the petitioning employer requires such education as an employment condition. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>STAPLE Act</title>
